    • Field Detail

      • airDebugLauncher

        public File airDebugLauncher
        Full path to the AIR Debug Launcher, adl.exe (Windows) or adl (Mac/Linux). This is mandatory.

      • airRuntimeDir

        public File airRuntimeDir
        The directory that has runtime.dll, or null to use the default.

      • airSecurityPolicy

        public File airSecurityPolicy
        The filename of the security policy to use, or null to use the default.

      • applicationContentRootDir

        public File applicationContentRootDir
        The directory to specify as the application's content root, or null to not tell ADL where the content root is, in which case ADL will use the directory of the application.xml file as the content root.

      • applicationArgumentsArray

        public String[] applicationArgumentsArray
        Array of command-line arguments for the user's program. These are specific to the user's program; they are not processed by AIR itself, just passed on to the user's app.

        Note, this class has both applicationArgumentsArray and applicationArguments. applicationArgumentsArray accepts an array of arguments, and passes them down as-is to the operating system. applicationArguments takes a single string, splits it into arguments, and passes the result to the operating system. You can use whichever one is more convenient for you; typically, one of these would be null. If both are non- null, then applicationArgumentsArray takes precedence, and applicationArguments is ignored.

      • applicationArguments

        public String applicationArguments
        Command-line arguments for the user's program. These are specific to the user's program; they are not processed by AIR itself, just passed on to the user's app.

        Note, see the comment above on applicationArgumentsArray.

      • airPublisherID

        public String airPublisherID
        The publisher ID to use; passed to adl's "-pubid" option. If null, no pubid is passed to adl.

      • profile

        public String profile
        The profile to pass to AIR 2.0's "-profile" argument, or null to omit the "-profile" argument.

      • screenSize

        public String screenSize
        The screensize argument to pass to AIR 2.0's "-screensize" option. A colon separated string indicating width and height of the screen in normal and fullscreen modes. Only relevant in the mobileDevice profile.

      • dpi

        public int dpi
        The dpi argument to pass to AIR 2.5's "-xscreenDPI" option. TODO: this is apparently only going to be used in 2.5

      • versionPlatform

        public String versionPlatform
        The version platform argument to pass to AIR's "-XversionPlatform" option. This overrides the three characters in Capabilities.os only for the runtime in the AIR SDK.

      • extDir

        public String extDir
        Directory to load native extensions from. Corresponds to the -extdir argument of ADL.

      • deviceExtDir

        public String deviceExtDir
        Directory to load native extensions from for devices. Corresponds to the -XdeviceExtDir argument of ADL.
